cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.SI 

This paper is about unbiased learning-to-rank in eCommerce search, which is a subfield of information retrieval (IR). Therefore, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel method for estimating click propensities, which involves statistical modeling and optimization, indicating that it may also belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computational linguistics (cs.CL), cybernetics (cs.CY), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
